00:35:22,955 --> 00:35:29,778
[SPEAKER_00]: We do not run any local transportation as a city, other than we contract out for the

383
00:35:30,288 --> 00:35:31,009
[SPEAKER_00]: school buses.

384
00:35:33,051 --> 00:35:41,538
[SPEAKER_00]: I heard noises about the school bus contract today and I was actually didn't have time to follow up and find out what was being talked about.

385
00:35:42,759 --> 00:35:47,784
[SPEAKER_00]: The general difficult, we don't own any of them, we contract for them.

386
00:35:48,420 --> 00:35:55,027
[SPEAKER_00]: So in order for them to be electric we would have to say in our RFP that we wanted electric school buses.

387
00:35:56,508 --> 00:36:02,694
[SPEAKER_00]: If people start pushing the city after a couple of years maybe they'll do it right this is the kind of thing that you have to play the long game.

388
00:36:04,135 --> 00:36:13,221
[SPEAKER_00]: Nobody is gonna turn around and electrify the school buses overnight, because again, they have to buy them, they have to acquire them, they have to have some place to charge them.

389
00:36:14,321 --> 00:36:20,264
[SPEAKER_00]: So all of this sort of plays into it, but people need the plan, and they're not gonna plan if they don't think the residents want it.

390
00:36:25,207 --> 00:36:27,288
[SPEAKER_00]: It's a school year, it's an election year.

391
00:36:27,308 --> 00:36:30,270
[SPEAKER_00]: You can bring it up when you're talking to potential school committee candidates.

392
00:36:38,170 --> 00:36:53,000
[SPEAKER_06]: Maybe what I should do is to modify this second point to sort of follow with the discussion we just had and then we'll send it out again.

393
00:36:53,180 --> 00:36:55,822
