874
01:27:30,106 --> 01:27:33,009
[SPEAKER_02]: It's a global market and it doesn't matter if

875
01:27:44,775 --> 01:27:50,260
[SPEAKER_09]: we're producing our own, it still enters into the global capitalist market.

876
01:27:50,901 --> 01:27:58,627
[SPEAKER_09]: So the price becomes the same as the global energy price for oil, for gas, for any commodity at all.

877
01:27:59,348 --> 01:28:02,811
[SPEAKER_09]: For coffee, for cotton, for any commodity.

878
01:28:04,973 --> 01:28:08,256
[SPEAKER_02]: Anyway, that's all I need to say about heat pumps at this time.

879
01:28:10,185 --> 01:28:23,318
[SPEAKER_03]: I would just briefly that I went through the process of deciding whether to get heat pumps and found it incredibly frustrating because everybody talked about something else to say.

880
01:28:24,379 --> 01:28:33,088
[SPEAKER_03]: And most of them, I talked to Luke and just assumed what he was telling me was accurate because he wasn't trying to sell me anything, wasn't going to make any money out of it.

881
01:28:33,702 --> 01:28:36,084
[SPEAKER_03]: But other than that, I got two or three different opinions about everything.

882
01:28:37,585 --> 01:28:45,271
[SPEAKER_03]: The cost saving was one that was pretty much agreed on, at least winter cost saving wasn't the reason to do this.

883
01:28:46,372 --> 01:28:50,795
[SPEAKER_03]: If you were using electric baseboard heating, you'd save some money, but you weren't gonna save any money on gas.

884
01:28:51,415 --> 01:28:58,401
[SPEAKER_03]: But whether you had to disconnect your furnace, how well they worked in cooler weather, how many you needed, how much of a rebate you could get,

885
01:28:59,670 --> 01:29:02,532
[SPEAKER_03]: I just found it so frustrating I gave up, which is my fault.

886
01:29:02,572 --> 01:29:03,673
[SPEAKER_03]: I shouldn't give up so easily.

887
01:29:04,174 --> 01:29:17,503
[SPEAKER_03]: But it is extraordinarily frustrating not being able to get a straight answer about anything, particularly when I had Luke's answers, which I regarded somewhat as gospel, because he's obviously knowledgeable and smart and wasn't trying to sell me anything.

888
01:29:17,864 --> 01:29:19,785
[SPEAKER_03]: So that's my experience with the process.

889
01:29:20,025 --> 01:29:23,628
[SPEAKER_03]: So if someone gets clear answers and wants to come by, I'll be happy to buy you dinner.

890
